{"title_page": "Buchi Babu (film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Buchi Babu \n| image          = Buchi_Babu.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| writer         = Dasari Narayana Rao<br />{{small|(story / screenplay / dialogues)}}\n| producer       = Venkat Akkineni<br />[[Nagarjuna Akkineni]]\n| director       = [[Dasari Narayana Rao]]\n| starring       = [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]]<br />[[Jaya Prada]]\n| music          = [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]\n| cinematography = P. S. Selvaraj\n| editing        = K. Balu\n| studio         = A. A Combines\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1980|3|19}}\n| runtime        = 155 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Buchi Babu''''' is a 1980 [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] [[comedy film]], produced by Venkat Akkineni, [[Nagarjuna Akkineni]] under the [[Annapurna Studios]] banner,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmiclub.com/movie/buchi-babu-1980-telugu-movie |title=Buchi Babu (Banner) |work=Filmiclub}}</ref> and directed by [[Dasari Narayana Rao]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/title/buchi-babu-telugu-movie/ |title=Buchi Babu (Direction) |work=Spicy Onion}}</ref> It stars [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]],  [[Jaya Prada]] in the lead roles<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gomolo.com/buchchi-babu-movie/16844 |title=Buchi Babu (Cast & Crew) |work=gomolo.com}}</ref> and music composed by [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knowyourfilms.com/film/Buchi-Babu/12351 |title=Buchi Babu (Music) |work=Know Your Films}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecinebay.com/movie/index/id/356?ed=Tolly |title=Buchi Babu (Review) |work=The Cine Bay}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nBuchi Babu (Akkineni Nageswara Rao) marries his maternal uncle Varahala Rao's (Raavi Kondala Rao) daughter Buchi (Jayaprada) in their childhood. At that time, Buchi Babu's parents (Prabhakar Reddy and Pushpalata) are needy in their in-laws (Gummadi and Nirmalamma) house. Gundabathula Achchamma (Suryakantham) maternal aunt to Buchi Babu, a shrew opposes this match, insults them badly and throws out the wedding chain from Buchi's neck. So, Buchi Babu has to leave their house along with his parents and safeguards the wedding chain. Years roll by, Buchi Babu's family becomes wealthy thereupon Varahala Rao arrives, explains them the present situation that Achchamma has destroyed the happiness in the family, made the children as spoil brats and also suffers her in-laws. Now to reform them Buchi Babu enters their house in disguise as a cook by the name Maryada Ramanna. Rest of the story is a comic tale that how Buchi Babu teaches them a lesson, acquires Buchi's love and set rights the entire family.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]] as Buchi Babu / Maryada Ramanna\n*[[Jaya Prada]] as Buchi\n*[[Mohan Babu]] as V. P. Rao\n*[[Dasari Narayana Rao]] as Buthula Bapaiah\n*[[Gummadi Venkateswara Rao|Gummadi]] as Buchi Babu's grandfather \n*[[M. Prabhakar Reddy|Prabhakar Reddy]] as Buchi Babu's father \n*[[Murali Mohan]] in a [[cameo appearance]]\n*[[Raja Babu (actor)|Raja Babu]] as Buthula Bapaiah's son\n*[[Chalam]] as Driver Seetapati\n*[[Raavi Kondala Rao]] as Varahala Rao \n*K. V. Chalam as Jayapapa's husband \n*[[Chalapathi Rao]] as Geetha's father \n*Raja as Rambabu\n*[[Suryakantam (actress)|Suryakantam]] as Gundabathula Achchamma\n*Pushpalata as Santha\n*[[Sujatha (actress)|Sujatha]] in a [[Cameo appearance]]\n*[[Rama Prabha]] as Hema \n*[[Geetha (actress)|Geetha]] as Geetha \n*Athili Lakshmi as Jayapapa\n*Dubbing Janaki as Geetha's mother \n*[[Nirmalamma]] as Buchi Babu's grandmother \n*[[Harish Kumar (actor)|Master Harish]] as young Buchi Babu \n*[[Tulasi (actress)|Baby Tulasi]] as young Buchi\n{{colend}}\n\n==Crew==\n*'''Art''': Bhaskar Raju\n*'''Choreography''': Saleem\n*'''Stills''': Mohanji - Jaganji\n*'''Playback''':  [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|SP Balu]], [[P. Susheela]], [[S. P. Sailaja]], Madhavapeddi Ramesh, Ramana, Pushpalata\n*'''Music''': [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]\n*'''Editing''': K. Balu\n*'''Cinematography''': P. S. Selvaraj\n*'''Producer''': Venkat Akkineni, [[Nagarjuna Akkineni]]\n*'''Story - Screenplay - Dialogues - Lyrics - Director''': [[Dasari Narayana Rao]] \n*'''Banner''': [[Annapurna Studios]]\n*'''Release Date''': 19 March 1980\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Buchi Babu\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1980\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     = 25:54\n| label      = SEA Records\n| producer   = [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]\n| prev_title = Sreevari Muchatlu\n| prev_year  = 1980\n| next_title = Pilla Zamindar\n| next_year  = 1980\n}}\n\nMusic composed by [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]. Lyrics were written by Dasari Narayana Rao. Music released on SEA Records Audio Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cineradham.com/telugu-audio/movie/979/Buchi%20Babu(1980)/ |title=Buchi Babu (Songs) |work=Cineradham}}</ref> \n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!S.No!!Song Title !!Singers !!length\n|-\n|1\n|\"Gundabathula Bujjamma\"\n|[[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|SP Balu]]\n|3:10\n|-\n|2\n|\"Kangaarauthondhi\"\n|G. Anand, [[P. Susheela]]\n|4:41\n|-\n|3\n|\"Chandamaama\"\n|Madhavapeddi Ramesh, P. Susheela\n|4:36\n|-\n|4\n|\"Sitharaala Thotalo\"\n|SP Balu,P. Susheela\n|3:17\n|-\n|5\n|\"Pasupupacha\"\n|P. Susheela, [[S. P. Sailaja]]\n|3:31\n|-\n|6\n|\"Vaalmiki Intilo\"\n|SP Balu\n|3:15\n|-\n|7\n|\"Yerra Koka Kattinaave\"\n|SP. Balu, Ramana\n|3:24\n|}\n\n==Others==\n* VCDs and DVDs on&nbsp;\u2014 VOLGA Videos, [[Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh|Hyderabad]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Dasari Narayana Rao}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by K. Chakravarthy]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Dasari Narayana Rao]]\n[[Category:1980s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:1980s comedy films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Buchi Babu \n| image          = Buchi_Babu.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| writer         = Dasari Narayana Rao<br />{{small|(story / screenplay / dialogues)}}\n| producer       = Venkat Akkineni<br />[[Nagarjuna Akkineni]]\n| director       = [[Dasari Narayana Rao]]\n| starring       = [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]]<br />[[Jaya Prada]]\n| music          = [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]\n| cinematography = P. S. Selvaraj\n| editing        = K. Balu\n| studio         = A. A Combines\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1980|3|19}}\n| runtime        = 155 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Buchi Babu''''' is a 1980 [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] [[comedy film]], produced by Venkat Akkineni, [[Nagarjuna Akkineni]] under the [[Annapurna Studios]] banner,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmiclub.com/movie/buchi-babu-1980-telugu-movie |title=Buchi Babu (Banner) |work=Filmiclub}}</ref> and directed by [[Dasari Narayana Rao]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/title/buchi-babu-telugu-movie/ |title=Buchi Babu (Direction) |work=Spicy Onion}}</ref> It stars [[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]],  [[Jaya Prada]] in the lead roles<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gomolo.com/buchchi-babu-movie/16844 |title=Buchi Babu (Cast & Crew) |work=gomolo.com}}</ref> and music composed by [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knowyourfilms.com/film/Buchi-Babu/12351 |title=Buchi Babu (Music) |work=Know Your Films}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecinebay.com/movie/index/id/356?ed=Tolly |title=Buchi Babu (Review) |work=The Cine Bay}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nBuchi Babu (Akkineni Nageswara Rao) gets married to his maternal uncle Varahala Rao's (Raavi Kondala Rao) daughter Buchi (Jayaprada) in their childhood. At that time, Buchi Babu's parents (Prabhakar Reddy & Pushpalata) are needy in their in-laws (Gummadi & Nirmalamma) house. Gundabathula Achchamma (Suryakantham) maternal aunt to Buchi Babu, a shrew opposes this match, insults them badly and throws out the wedding chain from Buchi's neck. So, Buchi Babu has to leave their house along with his parents and safeguards the wedding chain. Years roll by, Buchi Babu's family becomes wealthy thereupon Varahala Rao arrives, explains them the present situation that Achchamma has destroyed the happiness in the family, made the children as spoil brats and also suffers her in-laws. Now to reform them Buchi Babu enters their house in disguise as a cook by the name Maryada Ramanna. Rest of the story is a comic tale that how Buchi Babu teaches them a lesson, acquires Buchi's love and set rights the entire family.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Akkineni Nageswara Rao]] as Buchi Babu / Maryada Ramanna\n*[[Jaya Prada]] as Buchi\n*[[Mohan Babu]] as V. P. Rao\n*[[Dasari Narayana Rao]] as Buthula Bapaiah\n*[[Gummadi Venkateswara Rao|Gummadi]] as Buchi Babu's grandfather \n*[[M. Prabhakar Reddy|Prabhakar Reddy]] as Buchi Babu's father \n*[[Murali Mohan]] as [[cameo appearance|Special appearance]]\n*[[Raja Babu (actor)|Raja Babu]] as Buthula Bapaiah's son\n*[[Chalam]] as Driver Seetapati\n*[[Raavi Kondala Rao]] as Varahala Rao \n*K. V. Chalam as Jayapapa's husband \n*[[Chalapathi Rao]] as Geetha's father \n*Raja as Rambabu\n*[[Suryakantam (actress)|Suryakantam]] as Gundabathula Achchamma\n*Pushpalata as Santha\n*[[Sujatha (actress)|Sujatha]] as [[Cameo appearance|Special appearance]]\n*[[Rama Prabha]] as Hema \n*[[Geetha (actress)|Geetha]] as Geetha \n*Athili Lakshmi as Jayapapa\n*Dubbing Janaki as Geetha's mother \n*[[Nirmalamma]] as Buchi Babu's grandmother \n*[[Harish Kumar (actor)|Master Harish]] as Young Buchi Babu \n*[[Tulasi (actress)|Baby Tulasi]] as